                <div class="widgetBox">
                    <h3 class="cufon_text">What is Twitition?</h3>
                    <div class="boxTop pngfix"></div>
                    <div class="boxContent">


                        <h4>Twi·ti·tion <i>[twih-tish-uhn]</i></h4>
                        <p><i>noun	1. &ldquo;a formally drawn request, often bearing the names of a number of those making the request, that is addressed to a person or group of persons in authority or power, published via Twitter.&rdquo;</i></p>

                        <p>Twitition allows Twitter users to start petitions or 'Twititions' for something which they are passionate about.</p>

                        <p>Your followers can then sign Twititions by simply by clicking on the link in your tweet and share amongst their followers.</p>
                        <p><a href="/create/">Click here to get started</a> and before you know it you could be changing the world!</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="boxBottom pngfix"></div>
                </div>
